<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-7090] Possible resource leaks in hadoop core code</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7090</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is always a good practice to close the IO streams in a finally block.. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, look at the following piece of code in the Writer class of BloomMapFile &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;BloomMapFile .java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;synchronized&lt;/span&gt; void close() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.close();
      DataOutputStream out = fs.create(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(dir, BLOOM_FILE_NAME), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
      bloomFilter.write(out);
      out.flush();
      out.close();
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;If an exception occurs during fs.create or on any other line,  out.close() will not be executed..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following can reduce the scope of resorce leaks..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;BloomMapFile .java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;synchronized&lt;/span&gt; void close() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.close();
      DataOutputStream out = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;{
          out = fs.create(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(dir, BLOOM_FILE_NAME), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
          bloomFilter.write(out);
          out.flush();
      }&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;finally&lt;/span&gt;{
	 IOUtils.closeStream(out);
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 
</description>
